Please compile the following C program into RISC-V using the RV32I instruction set. If overflow is
encountered, please round the return into +âˆž as appropriate.

float silly_math3(float A){
return -A*1024;
}


#Single-Precision IEEE Format
silly_math: 
slli t2,a0,1
srli t2,t2, 24 #Pulling out the exponent 
addi t2, t2, 10 #adding 2^10 to the exponent
li t4, 255
bge t2,t4, overflow
li t3, 0x80000000
xor t2, t2,t3
mv a0,t2

overflow:
li a0, 0x7F800000 #Loading + Infinity


